remarks: "Fresison", one of the syllogisms of Aristotelian logic.  No ` ph ` is ` ps ` (PeM), and some ` ps ` is ` ch ` (MiS), therefore some ` ch ` is not ` ph ` (SoP).  (In Aristotelian notation, EIO-4:  PeM and MiS therefore SoP.) (Contributed by David A. Wheeler, 28-Aug-2016.) (Revised by David A. Wheeler, 2-Sep-2016.)
statement:
fresison.maj $e |- A. x ( ph -> -. ps ) $.
fresison.min $e |- E. x ( ps /\ ch ) $.
fresison $p |- E. x ( ch /\ -. ph ) $.
